        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — mesh convergence study",
        "description": "A systematic mesh convergence study must demonstrate that QoI change is <2% between the penultimate and final mesh refinement levels. Richardson extrapolation or GCI must be reported."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod-screw interface regions. GCI values for stiffness and yield force were 0.8% and 1.1% respectively, both below the 2% threshold. The production mesh (approx. 380 k elements, predominantly hex20) was selected at the converged level, achieving Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-nse",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The FEA model uses Ansys Mechanical's direct sparse solver (SPARSE) with double-precision arithmetic in a deterministic, implicit static analysis. No iterative solver convergence tolerance or explicit time-stepping error is present. Numerical solver error as a distinct credibility factor — addressing iterative residual drift or explicit stability — does not apply to this problem class. The ASME V&V 40 factor is therefore not-applicable."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-ue",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The validation study is executed by a single, tightly controlled modeling team (FDA OSEL) following a pre-approved simulation protocol. There is no end-user population who applies the model independently; the model is not distributed as a simulation tool for clinical users. The ASME V&V 40 use-error factor addresses variability introduced by diverse end-user populations applying the model without oversight, a scenario that is not present in this COU. The factor is therefore not-applicable."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-mf",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
