        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — traceable material and geometry data",
        "description": "All material properties and geometric dimensions used in the FEA must be traceable to measured data with documented uncertainty. Gradation 2 requires traceability; Gradation 3 requires uncertainty bounds reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Geometric dimensions were extracted from calibrated CMM measurements of production screws (±0.01 mm). Material properties (E, yield stress, tangent modulus) were measured from five tensile coupons per lot and reported with 95% confidence intervals. Input uncertainty was propagated through a Monte Carlo study (N=500 runs) to characterize QoI sensitivity, achieving Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-ts",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
