        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-cou1-tc",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — multiple loading configurations",
        "description": "Gradation 3 requires testing under at least two distinct loading configurations (e.g., varying offset distance or load angle) to characterize sensitivity of QoIs to test setup parameters."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single ASTM F1717-mandated offset distance (50 mm) and a single load angle (0°). While the single-condition protocol is consistent with the regulatory submission standard, it does not provide the multi-condition coverage required for Gradation 3. The shortfall is acknowledged; an offset rationale is provided in the decision record."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-eip",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
