        "description": "FEA boundary conditions (fixture geometry, load application point, constraint definitions) must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test setup. Gradation 2 requires documented mapping with photographic or engineering-drawing evidence."
      },
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions were defined directly from engineering drawings of the ASTM F1717 test fixture and verified against photographs of the assembled test setup. Load application point, fixture block geometry, and screw seating depth were matched to within measurement uncertainty. The mapping is documented in the simulation protocol with annotated figures."
