        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — E/uval metric",
        "description": "The validation metric E/uval must be below 1.96 for all primary QoIs, and percentage difference must be below 10%. Gradation 3 requires uncertainty-normalized comparison with explicitly reported uval."
      },
      "rationale": "E/uval values were 0.84 (stiffness), 1.12 (yield force), and 0.97 (force at 40 mm), all below 1.96. Percentage differences were 3.1%, 5.4%, and 4.2% respectively, all below 10%. Uncertainty in the validation metric was computed from experimental measurement uncertainty and model input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo, meeting Gradation 3."
